(482, 1, '2015-06-08 07:27:18', '2015-06-08 07:27:18', '[vc_row][vc_column][vc_column_text]\n<h3 class=\"tab-title\">Course Description</h3>\n<div class=\"js-simple-collapse\" data-more=\"Full details\">\n<div class=\"js-simple-collapse-inner\">\n\nDo you ever wish you could know what someone is thinking? Or perhaps you want to improve your own non-verbal communication? Body language is a great way to gain insights into how others think and feel, as well improve your everyday communication with others.\n\nThis body language course is based on scientifically-backed research, and is designed to teach you how to read people\'s nonverbal behavior and improve your own.\n\nWhether you are a business owner, parent, spouse, employee, human resources director, teacher or student, this course will change the way you interact with those around you.\n\nIf you have ever interacted with another person, this course will be useful to you because our everyday interactions are filled with secret nonverbal cues just waiting to be uncovered.\n\nWhy Is Body Language Important?\n\nUp to 93% of our communication is nonverbal. However, we often only think about the words we say, not how we say them. In this course, we will review the face, the body and how it expresses emotions and even talk a little bit about the lie detection.\n\nIn the Secrets of Body Language I give real life examples and tons of practical tips that you will be able to use immediately.\n\nIf You Don\'t Learn How to Decode Body Language Now, You\'ll Hate Yourself Later\n\nAt one point you will be on a date, in a business meeting, or in a negotiation and wish you know how to read body language. Invest the time in this course and you will be happy to have a leg up on your communication in the future.\n\nIf you wish you could begin to unravel the mysteries of body language, then enroll today in Secrets of Body Language now!\n\n</div>\n</div>\n[/vc_column_text][vc_custom_heading text=\"Course certificates\" font_container=\"tag:h2|text_align:center\" google_fonts=\"font_family:Montserrat%3Aregular%2C700|font_style:700%20bold%20regular%3A700%3Anormal\"][stm_color_separator][vc_row_inner][vc_column_inner width=\"1/2\"][stm_certificate image=\"1490\"][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width=\"1/2\"][stm_certificate image=\"1490\"][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column][vc_custom_heading text=\"Course overview\" font_container=\"tag:h3|text_align:left\" google_fonts=\"font_family:Montserrat%3Aregular%2C700|font_style:700%20bold%20regular%3A700%3Anormal\" css=\".vc_custom_1436944848385{margin-bottom: 30px !important;}\"][stm_course_lessons title=\" Section 1: Introduction\"][stm_course_lesson icon=\"fa-icon-stm_icon_teacher\" badge=\"free\" title=\"Introduction\" meta=\"Preview\" meta_icon=\"fa fa-youtube-play\"]Here is a brief overview to the course and what you will learn![/stm_course_lesson][stm_course_lesson icon=\"fa fa-female\" badge=\"preview\" title=\"Body Language Challenge \" meta=\"Preview\" meta_icon=\"fa fa-youtube-play\"]I have 2 body language challenges for you:\n\n1. I want you to test your skills from the beginning to the end of the course. We are going to watch 2 videos now and then watch them again at the end of the course, where we will slow them down and dissect the body language.\n\n2. Sign-Up to get free practice videos to test your skills:\n\n<a class=\"external-link\" href=\"http://www.scienceofpeople.com/subscribe\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">ScienceofPeople.com</a>\n\nReply to the first email and<strong> tell me what your biggest body language challenges are.</strong>[/stm_course_lesson][stm_course_lesson icon=\"fa-icon-stm_icon_teacher\" badge=\"quiz\" title=\"Test your first skills\" meta_icon=\"fa fa-pencil\"]We want to separate students with same skills on groups[/stm_course_lesson][/stm_course_lessons][stm_course_lessons title=\"Section 2: Foundations of Body Language\"][stm_course_lesson icon=\"fa fa-male\" title=\"Foundations of Body Language \" meta=\"Practice\" meta_icon=\"fa fa-angellist\"]Let\'s Review the foundations of where body language science comes from and how we study it.[/stm_course_lesson][stm_course_lesson icon=\"fa fa-male\" title=\"How the Brain Views the Body\" meta=\"Practice\" meta_icon=\"fa fa-angellist\"]This video gives an overview of how the brain reads body language.[/stm_course_lesson][stm_course_lesson icon=\"fa fa-male\" title=\"Where Does Body Language Come From?\" meta=\"Practice\" meta_icon=\"fa fa-angellist\"][/stm_course_lesson][/stm_course_lessons][stm_course_lessons title=\"Section 3: The Face and Microexpressions\"][stm_course_lesson icon=\"fa fa-child\" badge=\"free\" title=\"The Face and Microexpressions \"][/stm_course_lesson][stm_course_lesson icon=\"fa fa-eye\" badge=\"free\" title=\"Eye Behavior \"][/stm_course_lesson][stm_course_lesson icon=\"fa fa-header\" badge=\"free\" title=\"Head Behavior\"]Since we are starting at the top of the body, it is important to talk about some interesting head behavior and what it means in body language expression.[/stm_course_lesson][/stm_course_lessons][/vc_column][/vc_row]', 'The Secrets of Body  Language', 'Do you want to have more business success? Mastering body language is the missing ingredient for many business owners. Nonverbal communication can not only help you be more effective in your business dealings, but it can also give you an added edge above competitors.', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'the-secrets-of-body-language', '', '', '2015-06-08 07:27:18', '2015-06-08 07:27:18', '', 0, 'http://masterstudy.stylemixthemes.com/demo/?post_type=product&amp;p=482', 0, 'product', '', 0),
(486, 1, '2015-06-08 07:46:13', '2015-06-08 07:46:13', '[vc_row][vc_column][vc_column_text]\n<div id=\"what-you-get\" class=\"top-space-for-scroll\">\n<h3 class=\"tab-title\">What am I going to get from this course?</h3>\n<ul class=\"regular-list\">\n	<li>Over 91 lectures and 40.5 hours of content!</li>\n	<li>Work comfortably with Android Studio and the Android build tools</li>\n	<li>Understand the challenges and solutions to common problems that crop up in production quality Android development</li>\n	<li>Work with live APIs, including uploading images and handling authentication</li>\n	<li>Handle the Android application lifecycle correctly, and in a standard way</li>\n	<li>Leverage OO design patterns to simplify development</li>\n	<li>Have the experience and knowledge to to build production quality social networking applications</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<div id=\"who-should-attend\" class=\"top-space-for-scroll\"></div>\n[/vc_column_text][stm_multy_separator][vc_tta_tour][vc_tta_section title=\"Requirements\" tab_id=\"1436943387596-43cbc3df-3678\"][vc_column_text]\n<div id=\"requirements\" class=\"top-space-for-scroll\">\n<ul class=\"regular-list\">\n	<li>Willingness to learn design patterns and proper usage of an OO language</li>\n	<li>Basic programming ability, especially in a similar, statically typed language, such as C# or C++</li>\n	<li>All software is explained and installed on video</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<div id=\"what-you-get\" class=\"top-space-for-scroll\"></div>\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_tta_section][vc_tta_section title=\"Target audience\" tab_id=\"1436943387890-72c7e841-b181\"][vc_column_text]\n<div id=\"who-should-attend\" class=\"top-space-for-scroll\">\n<ul class=\"regular-list\">\n	<li>Beginner to advanced programmers</li>\n	<li>Experience in Java is not required, especially if the student already knows a similar language such as C#</li>\n	<li>Experience in Android, or any other mobile platform, is not required - we cover everything required to get set up in a modern development environment!</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<div id=\"curriculum\" class=\"top-space-for-scroll\" data-purpose=\"course-curriculum\"></div>\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_tta_section][/vc_tta_tour][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column][vc_custom_heading text=\"Course overview\" font_container=\"tag:h3|text_align:left\" google_fonts=\"font_family:Montserrat%3Aregular%2C700|font_style:700%20bold%20regular%3A700%3Anormal\" css=\".vc_custom_1436944848385{margin-bottom: 30px !important;}\"][stm_course_lessons title=\" Section 1: Introduction to Android Development\"][stm_course_lesson icon=\"fa-icon-stm_icon_teacher\" badge=\"free\" title=\"Introduction\" meta=\"Preview\" meta_icon=\"fa fa-youtube-play\"]This video covers the course, how to use the source code, and what we will be building![/stm_course_lesson][stm_course_lesson icon=\"fa fa-code\" badge=\"preview\" title=\"Setting up your Development Environment \" meta=\"Preview\" meta_icon=\"fa fa-youtube-play\"]This video shows how to get a complete Android development environment setup and ready to go![/stm_course_lesson][stm_course_lesson icon=\"fa-icon-stm_icon_teacher\" badge=\"quiz\" title=\"Test your first skills\" meta_icon=\"fa fa-pencil\"]We want to separate students with same skills on groups[/stm_course_lesson][/stm_course_lessons][stm_course_lessons title=\"Section 2: Beginning our Application\"][stm_course_lesson icon=\"fa fa-pencil\" title=\"Beginning your application\" meta=\"Practice\" meta_icon=\"fa fa-file-code-o\"]We kick off the development of the application by creating a handful of classes that we will be using throughout the series.[/stm_course_lesson][stm_course_lesson icon=\"fa fa-pencil\" title=\"Using GIT with Android Studio\" meta=\"Practice\" meta_icon=\"fa fa-code-fork\"]This video introduces using GIT with Android Studio. We also setup a BitBucket repository and connect it to our local one. Feel free to skip this video if you\'re already comfortable using GIT with Android Studio.[/stm_course_lesson][stm_course_lesson icon=\"fa fa-pencil\" title=\"A Soft Introduction to Fragments\" meta=\"Practice\" meta_icon=\"fa fa-code\"]This video demonstrates a use of a powerful Android feature - Fragments. We create a reusable login form that enables us to have different layouts on phones and tablet devices.[/stm_course_lesson][stm_course_lesson icon=\"fa fa-pencil\" title=\"Communicating with Fragments \" meta=\"Practice\" meta_icon=\"fa fa-qrcode\"]This video continues the previous one by showing a common and very powerful technique that allows a fragment to communicate with the activity that it is attached to.[/stm_course_lesson][stm_course_lesson icon=\"fa-icon-stm_icon_brain\" badge=\"quiz\" title=\"Testing your app\" meta=\"Test\" meta_icon=\"fa fa-check\"]In this lesson, we will test your app in native environment[/stm_course_lesson][/stm_course_lessons][/vc_column][/vc_row]', 'Introduction to Mobile Apps Development', 'Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit. Duis vestibulum turpis eu nunc volutpat vestibulum. Donec scelerisque arcu ac ante.', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'developing-mobile-apps', '', '', '2015-06-08 07:46:13', '2015-06-08 07:46:13', '', 0, 'http://masterstudy.stylemixthemes.com/demo/?post_type=product&amp;p=486', 0, 'product', '', 0),
(488, 1, '2015-06-08 07:47:17', '2015-06-08 07:47:17', '[vc_row][vc_column][vc_message message_box_style=\"solid-icon\" message_box_color=\"peacoc\" icon_fontawesome=\"fa fa-camera-retro\"]A to Z guide to becoming a professional photographer - know how to properly use a camera and apply composition concepts.[/vc_message][vc_column_text]\n<h3 style=\"margin: 0 0 20px 0;\">Have you always had a passion for taking pictures and thought about getting the proper photography training?</h3>\nPhotography is much more than simply taking a photo with your camera. There is a lot of technique and knowledge you need to know to perfectly capture moments.\n\nThis beginner course on photography will walk you through step by step every aspect you need to know to start improving your photography skills and potentially have your own photography business.\n\nIngred Shine has been a professional photographer and photography teacher for over 22 years. She\'ll serve as your guide through improving your photography skills.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column][vc_tta_tabs][vc_tta_section title=\"Course Targets\" tab_id=\"1436938259973-a86e9735-a51c\"][vc_column_text]\n<ul>\n	<li>Basics of Cameras</li>\n	<li>Basics of Photography</li>\n	<li>Point and Shoot Cameras</li>\n	<li>Retouring Pictures on the Camera</li>\n	<li>Image Size and Resolution</li>\n	<li>DSLR Cameras</li>\n	<li>How to Properly Take a Picture</li>\n	<li>White Balance and Noise</li>\n	<li>Camera Menu and Settings</li>\n	<li>Retouring, Exposure and More</li>\n	<li>iPhone Cameras</li>\n	<li>Focus, Brightness, Flash and Filters</li>\n	<li>The Exposure Triangle – Aperature, Shutter and ISO</li>\n	<li>Manual Shooting</li>\n	<li>Shooting Techniques and Lenses</li>\n	<li>Framing and Posing</li>\n	<li>Objects of Interest and Perspective</li>\n	<li>Rule of Thirds</li>\n	<li>Depth of Field</li>\n	<li>Lighting and Time of Day</li>\n</ul>\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_tta_section][vc_tta_section title=\"Target Audience\" tab_id=\"1436938260341-9eba3d71-7839\"][vc_column_text]\n<div id=\"who-should-attend\" class=\"top-space-for-scroll\">\n<ul class=\"regular-list\">\n	<li>These lectures are perfect for anyone are interested in photography but hasn\'t tried it out yet. You will be able to see the difference between a point &amp; shoot and a DSLR camera. This will help you gauge what level of photography you are comfortable starting at before purchasing any equipment.</li>\n	<li>As a whole, this course is great for people who enjoy taking pictures but want to take it to the next level. If you\'re an avid Instagram user, or you have a point &amp; shoot camera, this is just what you\'ve been looking for.</li>\n	<li>This course is NOT intended for photography professionals or photographers who are actively seeking side work. This course is a general introduction with excellent demonstrations of the camera and how to photograph people and objects. Most photographers who are already to making money from their craft will already know the majority of information presented in this course.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<div id=\"curriculum\" class=\"top-space-for-scroll\" data-purpose=\"course-curriculum\"></div>\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_tta_section][/vc_tta_tabs][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row css=\".vc_custom_1436959520228{margin-bottom: 10px !important;}\"][vc_column][vc_custom_heading text=\"Course review\" font_container=\"tag:h3|text_align:left\" google_fonts=\"font_family:Montserrat%3Aregular%2C700|font_style:700%20bold%20regular%3A700%3Anormal\"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column][stm_course_lessons title=\"Section 1: Getting Started\"][stm_course_lesson icon=\"fa fa-chevron-circle-right\" badge=\"preview\" title=\"Ingred Shine &amp; What You\'ll Learn\" meta=\"00:54\"][/stm_course_lesson][stm_course_lesson icon=\"fa fa-chevron-circle-right\" badge=\"preview\" title=\"Basics Of Cameras\" meta=\"00:54\" meta_icon=\"fa fa-camera\"][/stm_course_lesson][stm_course_lesson icon=\"fa fa-chevron-circle-righ