(525, 1, '2015-06-02 05:56:28', '2015-06-02 05:56:28', '[vc_row][vc_column][vc_column_text]\n<h2 class=\"tab-title\">Course Description</h2>\n<h3>A Modern Language Evolved from Objective C</h3>\nSwift is a multi-paradigm programming language developed by Apple for use with iOS and OS X. Designed to replace Objective C, work began on Swift in 2010 and the first mobile app was debuted in June 2014 at the Worldwide Developers Conference. Despite its goal of replacing Objective C, Swift is capable of working alongside the more dated Objective C language while using the Cocoa and Cocoa Touch frameworks.\n\nSwift is built with the LLVM compiler included in Xcode 6 beta, and uses the Objective-C runtime, allowing Objective-C, Objective-C++ and Swift code to run within a single program. During it’s debut, Swift was described as “<em>Objective C without the C</em>” by Apple’s VP of Software Engineering Craig Federighi.\n<h3>Contents and Overview</h3>\nThrough 95+ video lectures and 4 hours of content, you will be lead through setting up Swift locally, the basics of the language, how it compares to other common languages (including Objective C), and how to get started on new projects.\n\nThe course is designed to provide a comprehensive introduction to Swift, so that you can begin experimenting right away. Upon completion, you will understand the foundations of Swift code and will be able to develop custom applications. You will also get experience working with Xcode\'s new .playground file. By enrolling in this course you will be months ahead of other developers attempting learn the new Swift programming language by navigating Apple\'s 500-page instructional document.\n\nCourse material is regularly refreshed to include all of the newest updates and information, and since you’re granted lifetime access upon registering, you can rely on this course to keep your Swift skills on the cutting edge.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column][vc_tta_accordion][vc_tta_section title=\"What are the requirements?\" tab_id=\"1436963025094-f28cc4be-c05e\"][vc_column_text]\n<div id=\"requirements\" class=\"top-space-for-scroll\">\n<ul class=\"regular-list\">\n	<li>Developer access to Xcode 6 beta</li>\n	<li>A Mac computer that can run Xcode 6</li>\n	<li>Enrolled in a paid developer program (iOS or Mac is fine)</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<div id=\"what-you-get\" class=\"top-space-for-scroll\"></div>\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_tta_section][vc_tta_section title=\"What am I going to get from this course?\" tab_id=\"1436963025501-90d3f819-9895\"][vc_column_text]\n<div id=\"what-you-get\" class=\"top-space-for-scroll\">\n<ul class=\"regular-list\">\n	<li>Over 194 lectures and 12 hours of content!</li>\n	<li>Video walkthroughs showing you how to use Swift</li>\n	<li>Work with Xcode\'s new .playground file</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<div id=\"who-should-attend\" class=\"top-space-for-scroll\"></div>\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_tta_section][vc_tta_section title=\"What is the target audience?\" tab_id=\"1436963082052-807409d6-e14b\"][vc_column_text]\n<div id=\"who-should-attend\" class=\"top-space-for-scroll\">\n<ul class=\"regular-list\">\n	<li>Objective-C developers wanting to learn Swift</li>\n	<li>New programmers wanting to learn Swift</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<div id=\"curriculum\" class=\"top-space-for-scroll\" data-purpose=\"course-curriculum\"></div>\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_tta_section][/vc_tta_accordion][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column][vc_custom_heading text=\"Curriculum\" font_container=\"tag:h3|text_align:left\" google_fonts=\"font_family:Montserrat%3Aregular%2C700|font_style:700%20bold%20regular%3A700%3Anormal\" css=\".vc_custom_1436963177902{margin-bottom: 10px !important;}\"][stm_course_lessons title=\" Section 1: Swift - The Introduction\"][stm_course_lesson icon=\"fa-icon-stm_icon_teacher\" badge=\"free\" title=\"Welcome - What Will You Learn from This Course\" meta=\"Discovering\" meta_icon=\"fa-icon-stm_icon_seo_performance_up\"][/stm_course_lesson][stm_course_lesson icon=\"fa fa-youtube-play\" title=\"Getting Swift Set Up On Your Machine \" meta=\"05:55\" meta_icon=\"fa-icon-stm_icon_film-play\"]You can download Xcode for free now! You still have to register as a developer with Apple but follow the link on this blog https://developer.apple.com/swift/blog/[/stm_course_lesson][/stm_course_lessons][stm_course_lessons title=\"Section 2: The Basics\"][stm_course_lesson icon=\"fa fa-youtube-play\" title=\"Constants and Variables\" meta=\"05:34\" meta_icon=\"fa-icon-stm_icon_film-play\"][/stm_course_lesson][stm_course_lesson icon=\"fa fa-youtube-play\" title=\"Emoji Variable Names!? \" meta=\"Coding!\" meta_icon=\"fa fa-code\"][/stm_course_lesson][stm_course_lesson icon=\"fa fa-youtube-play\" title=\"Type annotations\" meta=\"Coding!\" meta_icon=\"fa fa-code\"][/stm_course_lesson][stm_course_lesson icon=\"fa fa-youtube-play\" title=\"Comments\" meta=\"Coding!\" meta_icon=\"fa fa-code\"][/stm_course_lesson][stm_course_lesson icon=\"fa fa-youtube-play\" title=\"Semi-colons\" meta=\"Coding!\" meta_icon=\"fa fa-code\"][/stm_course_lesson][stm_course_lesson icon=\"fa fa-youtube-play\" title=\"Integers\" meta=\"Coding!\" meta_icon=\"fa fa-code\"][/stm_course_lesson][stm_course_lesson icon=\"fa fa-youtube-play\" title=\"Type Aliases\" meta=\"Coding!\" meta_icon=\"fa fa-code\"][/stm_course_lesson][stm_course_lesson icon=\"fa fa-youtube-play\" title=\"Booleans\" meta=\"Coding!\" meta_icon=\"fa fa-code\"][/stm_course_lesson][stm_course_lesson icon=\"fa fa-youtube-play\" title=\"Tuples\" meta=\"Coding!\" meta_icon=\"fa fa-code\"][/stm_course_lesson][stm_course_lesson icon=\"fa fa-eye-slash\" badge=\"quiz\" title=\"The Basics - Quiz\" meta=\"Checkpoint\" meta_icon=\"fa fa-flag-checkered\"][/stm_course_lesson][/stm_course_lessons][/vc_column][/vc_row]', 'Swift Programming for Beginners', 'Swift is one of the fastest growing programming language and is now the most preferred technology for iOS and Mac Development. We at Eduonix have crafted a course to meet the growing demand of Quality Swift Programming for both beginners and Intermediate developers.', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'swift-programming-for-beginners', '', '', '2015-06-02 05:56:28', '2015-06-02 05:56:28', '', 0, 'http://masterstudy.stylemixthemes.com/demo/?post_type=product&amp;p=525', 0, 'product', '', 0),
